cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DS, cs.DB

The paper discusses a method for topic modeling, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), making cs.LG and cs.IR the most likely categories. The paper also mentions the use of parallelism and data decomposition, which are common techniques in distributed systems (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper applies the method to large corpora of conference papers and journal abstracts, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
